    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 139</em></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\"><img style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"No character may purchase a firearm unless she possesses the Gunsmithing feat and firearms are never considered Always Available\" src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" />Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 1,750 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 5 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 20 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1-2 (5 ft.); <strong>Capacity</strong> 2</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3>\n<p>This pistol has two parallel barrels; each barrel can be fired independently as a separate action, or both can be shot at once with the same action.</p>\n<p>If both barrels are shot at once, they must both target the same creature or object, and the pistol becomes wildly inaccurate, imposing a -4 penalty on each shot.</p>\n<p><strong>This is an early firearm.</strong></p>"
